6, 66], [36, 77], [36, 88], [36, 99], [36, 110], [36, 121], [36, 132], [36, 143], [36, 154], [36, 165], [37, 0], [37, 11], [37, 22], [37, 33], [37, 44], [37, 55], [37, 66], [37, 77], [37, 88], [37, 99], [37, 110], [38, 0], [38, 11], [38, 22], [38, 33], [38, 44]]}, "lines": {"text": ["Code of Conduct", "Story Factory provides an open, welcoming and safe environment for all young people, staff and", "volunteers participating in our programs.", "Its aim is to foster the development of writing skills and creativity in marginalised young people.", "At all times during Story Factory activities and when working for or representing Story Factory, staff", "and volunteers will:", "\u25cf treat people with respect, including staff, volunteers, young people, parents and teachers;", "\u25cf act honestly and with integrity;", "\u25cf act as positive role models to young people;", "\u25cf set and obey clear boundaries about appropriate behaviour with young people (see details", "below);", "\u25cf follow the Child-safe Child-friendly Policy;", "\u25cf comply with the Workplace Behaviour Policy;", "\u25cf only conduct tutoring under the direct supervision of a Story Factory representative who has", "satisfied a Working with Children Check and National Police Check;", "\u25cf report and act on complaints and/or any instances of inappropriate behaviour, breach of", "policy or suspected or observed abuse, by immediately notifying a Storyteller or other Story", "Factory staff member.", "Staff and volunteers:", "\u25cf will not develop any \u2018special\u2019 relationships with children that could be seen as favouritism,", "such as the offering of gifts or special treatment;", "\u25cf will not do things of a personal nature that a child can do for themselves, such as going to", "the toilet or changing clothes, and if a child needs such help, staff or volunteers will seek a", "family member or accredited carer to help them;", "\u25cf will not use personal phones or other electronic devices during workshops;", "\u25cf will not contact students outside of workshops, either in person or by phone, email, social", "media or any other electronic medium;", "\u25cf will not do anything, while providing their services, that may bring Story Factory into", "disrepute;", "\u25cf accept there may be risks associated with providing their services but agree they will not do", "anything to unreasonably compromise their own safety or the safety of others;", "\u25cf will participate in all identity verification checks, background security checks and other", "security checks (which may include inspecting their personal property) prior to their entry to", "and departure from any Story Factory activity or premises, and prior to their provision of any", "services \u2013 including completing a Working With Children Check and National Police Check;", "\u25cf will do anything required by law or Story Factory relating to the protection of children and", "abide by Story Factory\u2019s policies and guidelines for the safety of children as outlined in Story", "Factory\u2019s Child-safe Child-friendly Policy, this Code of Conduct, the Workplace Behaviour", "Policy and the Volunteer Agreement;"], "bbox": [[0.377768, 0.192208, 0.24327300000000007, 0.023883], [0.090604, 0.245513, 0.782937, 0.014595], [0.090604, 0.260536, 0.329073, 0.014595], [0.090604, 0.290581, 0.773973, 0.014595], [0.090604, 0.320626, 0.8050050000000001, 0.014595], [0.090604, 0.335648, 0.156852, 0.014595], [0.120805, 0.365693, 0.758831, 0.014595], [0.120805, 0.380716, 0.277271, 0.014595], [0.120805, 0.395738, 0.38903899999999997, 0.014595], [0.120805, 0.410761, 0.7663899999999999, 0.014595], [0.151007, 0.425783, 0.05945800000000001, 0.014595], [0.120805, 0.440805, 0.36847, 0.014595], [0.120805, 0.455828, 0.39683699999999994, 0.014595], [0.120805, 0.47085, 0.7785839999999999, 0.014595], [0.151007, 0.485873, 0.551176, 0.014595], [0.120805, 0.500895, 0.743792, 0.014595], [0.151007, 0.515918, 0.743222, 0.014595], [0.